You say, 'how can i further advance my reputation with the coldain?'<br>
Loremaster Borannin says 'Noggwin ! Thank Brell you're here. I was about to send one of my Lorekeepers looking for you. It appears that the information Tanik acquired is most perilous indeed. The Dain has called an emergency session of the council and I must attend. We don't have the luxury of waiting for an appropriate task to arise, you must advance as soon as possible. Unfortunately, I have neither the time, nor the components to fashion the next few shawls for you. Ask Rexx Frostweaver about the prayer shawl and follow his direction carefully. <br>
You say, 'what prayer shawl?'<br>
Rexx Frostweaver says 'Gather five strands of crystalline silk thread and combine them in a sewing kit to make a crystalline silk fiber. Take this container and combine a glowing shardworm bile with three of the fibers to form a piece of glowing crystalline silk. Five pieces of glowing crystalline silk sewn to your fur-lined shawl will yield a <br>
beautiful silk shawl. Become a master in the art of tailoring before risking all you've worked for and be sure to let me inspect your work when it's complete. <br>
<br>
<br>
The threads drop in velkators not as common as silks but not too bad. They are however no drop.<br>
You will need 75 threads and 5 biles to do this so bring a group and start farming.  No one is sure when it goes trivial but judging by the baking portion of this quest it may very well require a skill of 125 or so to complete which will make it very difficult.  Not sure what he means when he asks you to show it to him i am guessing that will lead to the 6th shawl.<br>
<br>
Please post your findings on trivials for making the fibers and what the final stats are for the shawl.  We all know this is alot harder than the ring quest so please dont turn  this into a mindless verant hates me flame.<br>
<br>
felecia<br>
Phantom Raiders<br>
